hopobject.body: Free medical insurance quikpills.com “I was so exhausted,” she says. “I thought I was going to have a heart attack.” In between all of this, Joyce phoned Mac to tell him what was happening. But she’d barely had time to convey the urgency of the situation when the electricity and, with it the phone connection, cut out. Mac leaped into his truck and drove eastwards. “By the time I got there all the roads had been closed off,” he says. “I was so worried. I had no idea where Joyce was.” As he approached the town, a huge wall of smoke loomed on the horizon; a thick grey canvas that enveloped the sky. “And it was right where we lived,” he says.
